(Cl+Me‚Äì Isothiazolinone containsmethylchloroisothiazolinone (MCI) andmethylisothiazolinone (MI), formaldehyde, and quaternium-15, also known as Q-15.) At work, you may find caine mix or one of its components in: ‚Ä¢ Manufacture of medicines containing benzocaine, tetracaine or dibucaine ‚Ä¢ First-aid analgesics and antiseptics with benzocaine, tetracaine or dibucaine At home, you may find caine mix or one of its components in: ‚Ä¢ Over-the-counter first-aid treatments for the pain and itching of injured skin ‚Ä¢ Prescription therapies for ear and eye inflammation ‚Ä¢ Sprays and lozenges for coughs and sore throats ‚Ä¢ Hemorrhoid treatments Benzocaine and related anesthetics are also found in some products used to treat athlete‚Äôs foot, calluses, warts and corns. You also may react to sunscreens and creams containing para-aminobenzoic acid (PABA) and to permanent hair dyes. I have to be sooooo careful.

‚Äã@johanaantonova740 Buying a K-beauty product physically in the West is almost always going to be more expensive, especially because K-beauty is trending these days. Between import costs, drug store upcharges, and trend uncharges, it doesn't surprise me to hear that k-beauty is 3x more expensive in your drugstore. The only way I can't get K-beauty without paying crazy upcharges near me is to either go to places like TJMaxx (they buy products in bulk and sell at discounted rates) or to save up to buy a bunch of products at once online to get free shipping. In my experience though, even if you're paying slightly more for K-beauty, the formulations are just so so much better than any low-mid priced skincare in the west.
